<en-note><div>Hint: You can go to a specific line number while opening a file:</div><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">vi</span> +<font color="#9437ff">line_number </font><font color="#0433ff"> <span style="font-style: italic;">filename.txt</span></font></div><div> <b>vi +</b><font color="#9437ff">15 </font><i><font color="#0433ff">sshd_config</font></i></div><div><i><font color="#0433ff"><br/></font></i></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">DELETE text(s)</span> </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">dw</span>    - delete a word ( from the current position to the end of the word) </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">d$</span>    - delete text from current position to the end of line</div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">dd </span>    - delete the current line </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">D </span>    - delete from the current position to the end of the current line </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">ndd </span>  - delete  n - lines </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">dG</span>    - delete from the current position to the end of the file </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">d1G</span>    - delete from the current position to the beginig of the file </div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">UNDO editing: </span> </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">u </span>      - undo the last command </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">U </span>      - undo the current line from all changed made on that line </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">:e! </span>    - edit again ( restarts to the state of the last save) </div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">MOVING cursor around: </span></div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">G</span>    - go to the end of the fil</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;"> 1</span><span style="font-weight: bold;">G</span>  - go to the beginning of the file</div><div> <span style="font-weight: bold;">n</span><span style="font-weight: bold;">G</span>  - go to <span style="font-weight: bold;">n </span>-th line</div><div>   </div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">0 </span>-  move the cursor to the beginning of the current line</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">$ </span>-  move the cursor to the end of the current line</div><div>   </div><div><font color="#797979"># “H” , “J” “K” ,”L”  ( All small letters)</font></div><div>&quot;<span style="font-weight: bold;">h</span>” (Left)  &quot;<span style="font-weight: bold;">j</span>” (Down) &quot;<span style="font-weight: bold;">k</span>” (Up) &quot;<span style="font-weight: bold;">l</span>” (Right)</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">CUT, COPY and PAST</span></div><div>   Note: You can use the DELETE options to CUT and then PAST with &quot;pp&quot; or &quot;P&quot; as shown below</div><div>   &quot;<b>yy</b>&quot;   - copy a current line</div><div>   &quot;<b>nyy</b>&quot;  - copy &quot;n&quot; lines (including the current line)</div><div>   &quot;<b>yw</b>&quot;   - copy a word</div><div>   &quot;<b>y$</b>&quot;   - copy from the current position to the end of the line</div><div>   &quot;<b>y1G</b>&quot;  - copy all lines from the current to the BEGINNING of the file</div><div>   &quot;<b>yG</b>&quot;   - copy all lines from the current to the END of the file</div><div>   &quot;<b>p</b>&quot;   - past below the current file</div><div>   &quot;<b>P</b>&quot;    - past above the current line</div><div><br/></div><div>6. <span style="font-weight: bold;">SEARCH and REPLACE</span></div><div>   &quot;:/&lt;word&gt;&quot; - search for &lt;word&gt;</div><div>   &quot;<b>:/</b>&quot;       - search again </div><div>   &quot;<b>r</b>&quot;        - replace a character under the cursor</div><div>   &quot;<b>nr</b>&quot;       - replace &quot;n&quot; characters from the current position   </div><div>   <span style="font-weight: bold;">:</span></div><div><span>%s</span>/<span>search</span>/<span>replace</span>/<span>g </span>          <font color="#797979"># Research and replace , &quot;<span>g</span>&quot; - mean all in the file</font></div><div>   <span style="font-weight: bold;">:</span></div><div><span>%s</span>/<span>search</span>/<span>replace</span>/<span>g</span><span>c</span>         <font color="#797979"> #Research and replace , &quot;<span>c</span>&quot; - mean confirm first</font></div><div>   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">SHOW LINE NUMBERS</span> </div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">:set </span>number  or <span style="font-weight: bold;">:set</span> nu</div><div><br/></div><div>                                                                                                                       <br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">SAVE and EXIT</span></div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">:w!</span> ,  <span style="font-weight: bold;">:q!</span> , <span style="font-weight: bold;">:wq</span> </div><div>  <span style="font-weight: bold;">:w </span><font color="#941100"><span style="font-style: italic;">new_file_name</span> </font>   <font color="#797979"># Save as a &quot;new_file_name</font></div><div><br/></div><div><font color="#797979">————— Hints for a coding ------------</font></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">TO JUMP</span> (between closing parenthesis, square brackets, curly braces)</div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">% </span> - brings the cursor to the matching position . For example, if your your cursor is on</div><div>          the top of &quot;{&quot; and you press &quot;%&quot; it will put the cursor on &quot;}&quot; or reverse versa.    </div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">How to change colours in &quot;.vimrc&quot; ?</span></div><div>Copy from /usr/local/share/vim/*/colors/</div><div>=&gt; cp /usr/local/share/vim/&lt;VIM_version/<span style="font-weight: bold;">desert.vim</span> /home/khasanov/<span style="font-weight: bold;">.vimrc</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">How To delete characters from the current position to the end of a line?</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;Shift&gt;</span><span style="font-weight: bold;">d</span></div></en-note>
